<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101049495294241></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101049495294241><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101049495294241>RE: Charm questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=101049495294241#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=86273><span id= >talnari</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 8th 8:02 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Charm is a great line.<br><br>I used to be very nervous about using it, but now find that with a rune on and some distance charm can work wonders.<br><br>I dont recommend rooting the pet, only because if your root holds out, you are wasting precious charm time.  <br><br>From personal experience, I like to get my charmed pet on something even to him.  Then, I sit just within casting distance from the fight, root what my pets on and then cast a DD or 2 to help my pet out so he is ensured victory.  <br><br>The great thing about this is that if charm breaks you have what your killing still rooted so you only have to deal with one aggro, who you can easily stun/recharm.  Plus. If your pet is fighting something equal to itself, his life is gonna get pretty low. Which means after your pet gets you exp from whatever he was killing, you can then earn exp from killing off your pet in one nuke once charm breaks.  <br><br>Giant pets ROCK!! and can earn great exp from soloing this way.<br><br>On a side note, Charisma IS important to Chanters for it directly effects mezzes.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
