<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100887790891333></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100887790891333><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100887790891333>RE: Soloing Enchanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=100887790891333#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27034><span id= >tourist</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 20th 2:51 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>  I tend to agree on the difficulty of soloing.  It takes a real commitment by the chanter to go for it.  Here's my recommendations (charm soloing):<br>  - Save up for tboots if you don't have jboots (soloing is soloing right?)<br>  - Get the cha gear up there to 185-200 (probly done that already for mez)<br>  - Buy alot of Jaspers LOL (I pref rune3 over rune4 for the price vs hps difference, but your choice)<br>  - Be patient and keep buffs fresh<br>  - Practice charm soloing in wide open places on non-sow mobs, until you get your timing vs distance down.  I used it effectively in the Ulthork camp in my 30s (grabbed a rhino and sent him raveging, hehe).  You can tash and charm him np from the max cast distance.  Once he engages on your victim mob you can slow/dot/whatever you like to the mob, then go sit at greater-than-max cast distance and med.  If charm breaks, and your pet is still the stronger of the two fighting, keep him targetted for recharm (see contigency plan below).  If you charm a yellow con and fight a just-red con, you can debuff the mob (I recommend not buffing your pet) and ensure the mob dies with your pet nearly dead (nuke if necessary).  Then you can invis and take your pet down with 1 nuke and reap double xp.  The spectres in Oasis were a gas for this, as they are also mezzable.<br>  - Don't start with HG's or other mobs that can cover the max cast distance faster than charm can be recast (I call that the 'nearly forked' case, lol).  When you feel ready for speedy mobs, charm one, plant him near a zone, pull another, let them go, if charm breaks and they are unmezzable, just zone unless you could nuke one dead in time.  It ain't worth the hassle otherwise, can't mez, can't charm, can't run, can aoe stun, but then there are resists... I rest my case).<br><br>  As with all chanter strats, we have a series of contingencies.  Be ready, and stick to your contingencies .  That's the part that takes alot of patience and skilling up<br><br>  Here's an ex of my contingency plan for the hardest charm soloing:<br>I have loaded:<br>tash<br>aoestun<br>mez<br>nuke<br>charm<br>memblur or aoememblur<br>slow/dot<br>gate (depending on situation)<br><br><br>  Mob charmed and beating on a mob<br>  Charm breaks: I try to recharm<br>  Charm resists: I try to outrun both and recharm my pet back<br>  Can't outrun: I mez one of them (with long mez), then the other, then charm.<br>  Can't mez, and they are outrunning me (this is the time to abort):  aoe stun, run and either memblur and hope he doesn't reaggro, gate out or nuke down if mob almost dead and try to charm/memblur the other, and either start the process over, or plant it and gate/run/start over.<br>  Mobs are both pretty alive:  Stun/Run to zone and try again with your health and mana mostly in tact.<br>  Can't run to zone in time:  Keep with the charm and/or memblur, maybe it'll stick and retaunt other mob before you die.<br><br>  The last one is not a pretty sight, but your blood will be pumping!  Also, if you stick with it, you'll have levelling without aid.<br>  Also, if you really commit yourself to this, I find it helps your grouping skills in emergency situations.  Many chanters never charm so they suck at it.  This is great practice and can turn the tide on a FPW.<br><br>  This is just an example, I'd love others' views on this to help me be a better chanta!  Specially using spells I haven't gotten to yet.<br><br>Justu Justinthyme<br>paltry illusionist<br>40th fizzle<br>Kempers Arcanum<br>Tholuxe Paells<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
