	   <tr><td colspan=2>Like Zeph said you can use Illusion: Earth Ele once you get 24.  That's the only method I have first-hand experience with and how I got most of my mana spells.<br><br>Earlier in my days I paid a druid to go in wolf form and buy my first spell.  So, evidentally that works as well.<br><br>The third method I've heard of sounds much scarier.  Apparently, Alliance will get you down to 'dubious' with the brownie guards.  So you can at least pass into the huts.  Once inside, cast minor illusion on yourself while standing next to the merchant and you will now con indifferent.  Buy your spell(s) and gate the hell outta dodge.  I have never ever tested or heard from anybody else who has tried this, so I really have no idea if it actually works.  In other words, use with caution.<br><br>Those are the three methods that I have heard of, there may be others but I'm not aware of any.<br><br>-Yizzelar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
